## Development

### Running Tests

```bash
# Install dev dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run all tests
python -m pytest tests/ -v

# Skip slow tests (embedding model download)
python -m pytest tests/ -v -m "not slow"
```

### Project Structure

```
membrane/
├── pyproject.toml                    # Package definition
├── .env.example                      # Configuration template
├── README.md                         # This file
├── src/
│   └── membrane/
│       ├── __init__.py               # Package version (2.0.0)
│       ├── __main__.py               # Entry point with Walrus/Sui init
│       ├── config.py                 # Settings (local + Walrus + Sui)
│       ├── server.py                 # MCP server — 9 tools
│       ├── db.py                     # SQLite metadata-only schema
│       ├── models.py                 # Pydantic data models
│       ├── walrus_client.py          # Walrus HTTP API client
│       ├── sui_client.py             # Sui proof client
│       ├── memory_manager.py         # Memory lifecycle orchestration
│       ├── artifact_manager.py       # Artifact lifecycle orchestration
│       ├── retrieval.py              # Metadata-first hybrid search
│       └── security.py              # Encryption + hashing + verification
└── tests/
    ├── conftest.py                   # Shared fixtures (fake Walrus/Sui)
    ├── test_walrus_client.py         # Walrus client tests
    ├── test_sui_client.py            # Sui client tests
    ├── test_memory_manager.py        # Memory lifecycle tests
    ├── test_artifact_manager.py      # Artifact lifecycle tests
    ├── test_retrieval.py             # Retrieval engine tests
    ├── test_security.py              # Security layer tests
    └── test_server.py                # End-to-end MCP tool tests
```

### Memory Object Format (stored in Walrus)

```json
{
  "memory_id": "uuid",
  "namespace": "research-agent",
  "owner": "wallet-address",
  "created_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00",
  "updated_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00",
  "type": "memory",
  "content": "memory content here",
  "metadata": {
    "tags": ["research", "important"],
    "source": "agent",
    "extra": {}
  }
}
```

### SQLite Schema (metadata only)

```sql
-- No content column — content lives in Walrus
memories (memory_id, namespace, owner, tags, timestamp, walrus_blob_id, content_hash, proof_id, embedding)
artifacts (artifact_id, walrus_blob_id, owner, filename, content_type, tags, timestamp, content_hash)
proofs (proof_id, sui_tx_hash, memory_id, content_hash, created_at)
```
